mes}}\n|{{flagIOC2medalist|[[Mahan Bajrang]]|IRI|2002 West Asian Games}}\n|-\n|{{flagIOC2medalist|[[Mohammad Abu-Saleh]]|JOR|2002 West Asian Games}}\n|}\n\n==Medal table==\n{{Medals table\n | caption        = \n | host           = \n | flag_template  = flagIOC2team\n | event          = 2002 West Asian Games\n | team           = \n | gold_KUW = 6 | silver_KUW = 0 | bronze_KUW = 3\n | gold_IRI = 2 | silver_IRI = 3 | bronze_IRI = 3\n | gold_SYR = 2 | silver_SYR = 2 | bronze_SYR = 3\n | gold_KSA = 1 | silver_KSA = 0 | bronze_KSA = 1\n | gold_JOR = 1 | silver_JOR = 0 | bronze_JOR = 1\n | gold_YEM = 0 | silver_YEM = 0 | bronze_YEM = 3\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20090915175231/http://www.westasiangames.com/second_wagf.asp Official website]\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20100613083050/http://ocasia.org/Game/GameParticular.aspx?GPCode=46 Olympic Council of Asia - 2002 West Asian Games]\n\n{{Events at the 2002 West Asian Games}}\n\n[[Category:2002 West Asian Games]]\n[[Category:2002 in gymnastics|West Asian Games]]\n[[Category:Gymnastics at the West Asian Games|2002]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox sports competition event\n| event       = Gymnastics\n| games       = 2002 West Asian Games\n| image       = Gymnastics (artistic) pictogram.svg\n| image_size  = 100px\n| venue       = Yarmouk Hall\n| date        = 10\u201312 April\n| prev        = \n| next        = [[Gymnastics at the 2005 West Asian Games|2005]]\n}}\n'''[[Artistic gymnastics]]''' at the [[2002 West Asian Games]] was held at Yarmouk Hall, [[Kuwait City]], [[Kuwait]] from 10 April 2002 to 12 April 2002.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u0645\u0633\u0643 \u0627\u0644\u062e\u062a\u0627\u0645 \u0644\u0623\u0628\u0637\u0627\u0644 \u0627\u0644\u0643\u0648\u064a\u062a \u0641\u064a \u0627\u0644\u062c\u0645\u0628\u0627\u0632 |url=http://www.alazraq.com/parts/show.php?page=article.php&a_id=23873 |publisher=alazraq.com |accessdate=31 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nIt had a men's only programme containing 8 events. A total of 6 nations (Iran, Syria, Kuwait, Saudi Arabia, Jordan and Yemen) participated.\n\n==Medalists==\n{|{{MedalistTable|type=Event}}\n|-\n|Team\n|{{flagIOC2|KUW|2002 West Asian Games}}<br />[[Ahmad Al-Duraia]]<br />[[Fahad Al-Ghannam]]<br />[[Ahmad Al-Herz]]<br />[[Saqer Al-Mulla]]<br />[[Mohammad Al-Omran]]<br />[[Nayef Dashti]]<br />[[Bader Mohammad]]\n|{{flagIOC2|IRI|2002 West Asian Games}}<br />[[Mahmoud Arab]]<br />[[Mahan Bajrang]]<br />[[Mohammad Hadi Ghasemi]]<br />[[Ahmad Majdi]]<br />[[Mehdi Niroumand]]<br />[[Mohammad Reza Samaei]]<br />[[Ali Shariati (gymnast)|Ali Shariati]]\n|valign=top|{{flagIOC2|SYR|2002 West Asian Games}}<br />[[Ahmad Amir Abdulkafi]]<br />[[Louay Al-Heraki]]<br />[[Amer Attar]]<br />[[Fadi Bahlawan]]<br />[[Mohammad Daher]]<br />[[Sadeq Daher]]\n|-\n|rowspan=2|Individual all-around\n|rowspan=2|{{flagIOC2medalist|[[Saqer Al-Mulla]]|KUW|2002 West Asian Games}}\n|{{flagIOC2medalist|[[Mohammad Hadi Ghasemi]]|IRI|2002 West Asian Games}}\n|rowspan=2|''Shared silver''\n|-\n|{{flagIOC2medalist|[[Fadi Bahlawan]]|SYR|2002 West Asian Games}}\n|-\n|rowspan=3|Floor\n|rowspan=3|{{flagIOC2medalist|[[Mohammad Hadi Ghasemi]]|IRI|2002 West Asian Games}}\n|rowspan=3|{{flagIOC2medalist|[[Fadi Bahlawan]]|SYR|2002 West Asian Games}}\n|{{flagIOC2medalist|[[Ahmad Al-Herz]]|KUW|2002 West Asian Games}}\n|-\n|{{flagIOC2medalist|[[Maki Al-Mubiareek]]|KSA|2002 West Asian Games}}\n|-\n|{{flagIOC2medalist|[[Nashwan Al-Harazi]]|YEM|2002 West Asian Games}}\n|-\n|rowspan=2|Pommel horse\n|{{flagIOC2medalist|[[Nayef Dashti]]|KUW|2002 West Asian Games}}\n|rowspan=2|''Shared gold''\n|rowspan=2|{{flagIOC2medalist|[[Nashwan Al-Harazi]]|YEM|2002 West Asian Games}}\n|-\n|{{flagIOC2medalist|[[Saqer Al-Mulla]]|KUW|2002 West Asian Games}}\n|-\n|rowspan=3|Rings\n|{{flagIOC2medalist|[[Sadeq Daher]]|SYR|2002 West Asian Games}}\n|rowspan=3|''Shared gold''\n|{{flagIOC2medalist|[[Mahan Bajrang]]|IRI|2002 West Asian Games}}\n|-\n|{{flagIOC2medalist|[